org.concordion.ext

Class StoryboardExtension

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.concordion.ext.StoryboardExtension
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.concordion.api.extension.ConcordionExtension

    public class StoryboardExtension
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.concordion.api.extension.ConcordionExtension
    The Storyboard extension provides the capability to embed a series of 'cards' containing screenshots or data (text, xml, or html) in a panel at the bottom of the specification.

    Further information can be found in the Specification.

      • setAppendMode

        public StoryboardExtension setAppendMode(StoryboardExtension.AppendTo appendMode)
        Set how items are added to the storyboard
        • Append to end of Storyboard (original behaviour)
        • If item is added within currently executing Example Command append to example element, otherwise append to Storyboard (default)
        • If item is added within currently executing Example Command append to new section container in Storyboard, otherwise append to Storyboard
        Parameters:
        appendMode - The card append mode
        Returns:
        A self reference

      • setAddCardOnThrowable

        public StoryboardExtension setAddCardOnThrowable(boolean value)
        Sets whether a card will be added to the storyboard when an uncaught exception occurs in the test. Defaults to true. If screenshotTaker is set then it will take a ScreenshotCard, else it will add a NotificationCard
        Parameters:
        value - true to add a card when an uncaught exception occurs in the test, false to not add a card.
        Returns:
        A self reference

      • setAddCardOnFailure

        public StoryboardExtension setAddCardOnFailure(boolean value)
        Sets whether a card will be added to the storyboard when a failure occurs in the test. Defaults to true. If screenshotTaker is set then it will take a ScreenshotCard, else it will add a NotificationCard
        Parameters:
        value - true to add a card when a failure occurs in the test, false to not add a card.
        Returns:
        A self reference

      • setSupressRepeatingFailures

        public StoryboardExtension setSupressRepeatingFailures(boolean value)
        if setAddCardOnFailure(boolean) is true then will optionally ignore second or subsequent failure. If using the Example command then each example will be treated separately.
        Parameters:
        value - true to not add card on second, or subsequent, failure (default behaviour), false to add a card for every failure.
        Returns:
        A self reference

      • setScreenshotTaker

        public StoryboardExtension setScreenshotTaker(ScreenshotTaker screenshotTaker)
        Set a screenshot taker. If not set then the storyboard extension cannot take screenshots. For a non gui application this is the most appropriate behaviour and you will not want to change this. For GUI applications you can either:
        • Use RobotScreenshotTaker which will take a shot of the full visible screen
        • See the demo application for an example implementation of a custom SeleniumScreenshotTaker
        Parameters:
        screenshotTaker - Takes screenshots of the system under test
        Returns:
        A self reference

      • removeScreenshotTaker

        public StoryboardExtension removeScreenshotTaker()
        Removes the screenshot taker so no further screenshots will be taken.
        Returns:
        A self reference

      • setTakeScreenshotOnExampleCompletion

        public StoryboardExtension setTakeScreenshotOnExampleCompletion(boolean value)
        When an example completes a screenshot of the current page will be automatically added to the storyboard - as long as the screenshot taker has been set.

        If not using the example command then final screenshots must be added manually.

        Parameters:
        value - true to take screenshot (default), false to not take screenshot
        Returns:
        A self reference

      • setSkipFinalScreenshotForCurrentExample

        public StoryboardExtension setSkipFinalScreenshotForCurrentExample()

        Returns:
        A self reference
